sentences: Ronnie Foster (born May 12, 1950) is an American funk and soul jazz organist, and record producer.
His albums recorded for Blue Note Records in the 1970s have gained a cult following after the emergence of acid jazz.
Foster was born in Buffalo, New York, on May 12, 1950.
